# mbX 2.1 Beta

[![CRAN status](https://www.r-pkg.org/badges/version/mbX)](https://cran.r-project.org/package=mbX)  
![Lifecycle: Beta](https://img.shields.io/badge/lifecycle-beta-orange.svg)

A comprehensive R package for **cleaning**, **statistical analysis**, and **visualization** of microbiome sequencing data (16S-rRNA). Supports CSV, TXT, and Excel formats, and offers easy aggregation at any taxonomic level.

---

## ⚙️ What’s New in 2.1 Beta

- **Import fix** for `pivot_longer()`: now explicitly imports **`tidyr::pivot_longer()`**, so `ezviz()` no longer fails on certain metadata factors (e.g. “Collector”).
- Minor documentation updates and CRAN‐style namespace improvements.
- Retains all features from **2.0**, including:
  - `ezclean()` – full preprocessing pipeline
  - `ezstat()`  – Kruskal–Wallis, Dunn tests, CLD summaries, boxplots
  - `ezviz()`   – stacked‐bar visualization with flexible `top_taxa`/`threshold` options

---
